<note class="clinical-tip" id="note-00001">
<title>Atypical Antipsychotic for Bipolar Disorder</title>
<para id="para-00007">In December 2021, the FDA approved <term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00002">lumateperone</term> (<term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00003">Caplyta</term>) for bipolar depression. The drug is an atypical antipsychotic. It can be used as a monotherapy or in combination with lithium or valproate. It is available as a once-daily oral pill that needs no dose changes.</para>
</note>
</section>
