<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center"><term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00006">Carbamazepine</term><newline/>
(<term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00007">Tegretol</term>)</entry>
<entry valign="top" align="left"><emphasis effect="italics">Adults and children >13 years:</emphasis> Initial dose: 200 mg orally twice daily (tablet); may increase by up to 200 mg/day in divided doses on a weekly basis. Maximum dose: 1200 mg in adults and 1000 mg in children 13–15 years. Therapeutic range: 4–12 mg/L.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center"><term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00008">Lamotrigine</term><newline/>
(<term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00009">Lamictal, Subvenite</term>)</entry>
<entry valign="top" align="left"><emphasis effect="italics">Monotherapy:</emphasis> First 2 weeks, 25 mg/day orally; week 3, increase to 50 mg/day; week 5 increase to 100 mg/day; week 6 increase to 200 mg/day (maximum).<newline/>
<emphasis effect="italics">As an adjunct to valproic acid:</emphasis> First 2 weeks, 25 mg orally every other day; week 3 increase to 25 mg/day; week 5 increase to 50 mg/day; week 6 increase to 100 mg/day. Therapeutic range: 3–14 mcg/mL.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center"><term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00010">Valproic acid, divalproex sodium</term><newline/>
(<term class="no-emphasis" id="term-00011">Depakote, Depakote ER</term>)</entry>
<entry valign="top" align="left"><emphasis effect="italics">Acute mania in adults:</emphasis> Initial dose: 1000 mg/day; increase dose rapidly. Maximum dose: 60 mg/kg/day.<newline/>
<emphasis effect="italics">Less acute mania in adults:</emphasis> Initial dose: 200–500 mg; titrate upward as tolerated. Therapeutic range: 50–100 mcg/mL.</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
